task: Final cohesion pass — per-track color glow on glass + reactive accent breathing

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/ParticipantList.vue
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/styles/glass.css

context: |
  With backdrop (T01), accent (T02), and glass chrome (T03–T05) in place, this is
  the polish task that sells the "premium audio app" feel:

    a) Each participant track has a .color (per-peer hue). The selected/local
       track currently gets a flat blue tint. Make the glass track row pick up
       its OWN peer color as a soft inset glow so the track list reads like lit
       channel strips on glass.
    b) The local ("you") track should subtly breathe (slow pulse) to feel alive,
       echoing sdui-proto's a-pulse ambient language — but gentle, not noisy.
    c) Respect prefers-reduced-motion (glass.css already reduces blur there;
       extend it to disable the pulse).

steps:
  1. ParticipantList: on .lp-track.selected (local) and on hover for remote
     tracks, add a left-edge / inset glow using the row's peer color. The color
     is available via the inline :style on .lp-track-color (p.color) — expose it
     to the row, e.g. set `--track-glow: <p.color>` as an inline style on the
     .lp-track element, then in scoped CSS:
       box-shadow: inset 3px 0 0 var(--track-glow),
                   inset 0 0 24px -8px var(--track-glow);
  2. Add a gentle breathing keyframe for the local track (opacity/glow only,
     ~3s ease-in-out infinite), gated behind a class so only the "you" row uses it.
  3. glass.css @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce): also set the breathing
     animation to none.
  4. Final visual audit (document in done): backdrop + accent + glass + glow all
     speak violet/indigo, Logic chrome intact, per-track color still distinct.

deps: T01–T05 (this is the closing polish; it assumes the system is in place).

done:
  - Local track glows in its own peer color and breathes gently.
  - Remote track rows pick up their color on hover (inset glow).
  - prefers-reduced-motion disables the breathing pulse.
  - Per-peer color identity preserved (the color bar still distinct).
  - No layout shift; compiles; dev server clean.
  - SIGN-OFF note: the three layers (particles / glass / Logic) read as one
    cohesive premium audio UI.
